title._content: An unknown child dressed as a sailor

description._content: ID number: P04040.003 Photographer: Unknown Date Made: Unknown Melbourne, Port Melbourne: Studio portrait of an unidentified child dressed in a sailor suit. The child leans on a post, reminiscent of a mast, with one arm around it, legs crossed casually, the other hand grasps a rope that hangs from the top of the pole. A sailor suit was typical clothing for young children of the 19th century. Rights Info: No known copyright restrictions. This photograph is from the Australian War Memorial's collection www.awm.gov.au Persistent URL: www.awm.gov.au/collection/P04040.003
